987	## 3. Accessibility
988	
989	### 3.1 ARIA Roles, States, and Properties
990	
991	| Property           | Element            | Value                                                                            |
992	| ------------------ | ------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
993	| `role`             | `Control`          | `grid` (enables proper AT navigation between tags and their delete actions)      |
994	| `aria-labelledby`  | `Control`          | Label id                                                                         |
995	| `role`             | `Tag`              | `row`                                                                            |
996	| `role`             | `TagText`          | `gridcell`                                                                       |
997	| `role`             | `TagDeleteTrigger` | `gridcell` (contains the remove button)                                          |
998	| `aria-describedby` | `Input`            | Description + ErrorMessage ids                                                   |
999	| `aria-label`       | `Tag`              | `"{value}"`                                                                      |
1000	| `aria-disabled`    | `Tag`              | When tag or group is disabled                                                    |
1001	| `aria-label`       | `TagDeleteTrigger` | `"Remove {value}"`                                                               |
1002	| `aria-label`       | `ClearTrigger`     | `"Remove all tags"`                                                              |
1003	| `aria-describedby` | `Tag`              | ID of shared visually hidden text: "Press Delete to remove" (localized via i18n) |
1004	
1005	### 3.2 Keyboard Interaction
1006	
1007	| Key          | In Input                           | On Tag                     |
1008	| ------------ | ---------------------------------- | -------------------------- |
1009	| Enter        | Add current input as tag           | —                          |
1010	| Backspace    | If empty: focus last tag           | Remove tag                 |
1011	| Delete       | —                                  | Remove tag                 |
1012	| ArrowLeft    | If cursor at start: focus last tag | Focus previous tag         |
1013	| ArrowRight   | —                                  | Focus next tag or input    |
1014	| Escape       | Clear input                        | Deselect tag → focus input |
1015	| Double-click | —                                  | Enter edit mode on tag     |
1016	
1017	### 3.3 Screen Reader Announcements
1018	
1019	When a tag is removed, screen reader users must be informed of the removal and the
1020	resulting focus location:
1021	
1022	- **Live region announcement**: On tag deletion, emit an `aria-live="polite"` announcement:
1023	  `"Removed {tag_label}"` (localized via `Messages`).
1024	- **Tag `aria-label`**: Each Tag part MUST have `aria-label="{tag_label}, press Delete to remove"`
1025	  (localized via `Messages.delete_hint`), combining the tag value with the
1026	  removal instruction.
1027	- **Max count reached**: When `ctx.value.get().len() >= ctx.max.unwrap_or(usize::MAX)`,
1028	  announce `"Maximum of {max} tags reached"` via the live region. The input SHOULD also
1029	  set `aria-disabled="true"` to indicate no more tags can be added.
1030	- **Focus management after removal**: Focus follows the existing `focus_tag` effect —
1031	  moves to the adjacent tag (same index, clamped to `len - 1`), or to the input if no
1032	  tags remain. This behavior is already implemented in the `RemoveTag` and
1033	  `RemoveTagAtIndex` transitions above.
1034	
1035	## 4. Internationalization
1036	
1037	### 4.1 Messages
1038	
1039	```rust
1040	#[derive(Clone, Debug)]
1041	pub struct Messages {
1042	    /// Template for tag delete trigger label (default: "Remove {value}")
1043	    pub remove_tag_label: MessageFn<dyn Fn(&str, &Locale) -> String + Send + Sync>,
1044	    /// Clear all trigger label (default: "Remove all tags")
1045	    pub clear_all_label: MessageFn<dyn Fn(&Locale) -> String + Send + Sync>,
1046	    /// Visually hidden instruction (default: "Press Delete to remove")
1047	    pub delete_hint: MessageFn<dyn Fn(&Locale) -> String + Send + Sync>,
1048	    /// Count label when `max_tags` is set (default: "{current} of {max} tags").
1049	    pub count_label: MessageFn<dyn Fn(usize, usize, &Locale) -> String + Send + Sync>,
1050	}
1051	
1052	impl Default for Messages {
1053	    fn default() -> Self {
1054	        Self {
1055	            remove_tag_label: MessageFn::new(|value, _locale| format!("Remove {}", value)),
1056	            clear_all_label: MessageFn::static_str("Remove all tags"),
1057	            delete_hint: MessageFn::static_str("Press Delete to remove"),
1058	            count_label: MessageFn::new(|current, max, _locale| format!("{} of {} tags", current, max)),
1059	        }
1060	    }
1061	}
1062	
1063	impl ComponentMessages for Messages {}
1064	```
1065	
1066	All hardcoded `aria-label` values in `TagDeleteTrigger` and `ClearTrigger` MUST read from this struct.
1067	
1068	- **Delimiter**: Default `,` — may be configured per locale (some locales use `;`).
1069	- **Tag labels**: `"Remove {value}"` — localized via `Messages.remove_tag_label`.
1070	- **RTL**: Tag order renders right-to-left; ArrowLeft/Right reversed visually.
1071	- **Max count message**: `"{current} of {max} tags"` — localized with plural rules via `Messages.count_label`.
1072	
1073	## 5. Form Integration
1074	
1075	- **Hidden input**: The `HiddenInput` part is a `<input type="hidden">` whose `value` is the joined tag list (`ctx.value.get().join(&ctx.delimiter)`). The `name` attribute is set from `Props.name`.
1076	- **Validation states**: `aria-invalid="true"` on `Root` when `invalid=true`. The `ErrorMessage` part is linked via `aria-describedby` on the `Input`.
1077	- **Per-tag validation**: Use the forms foundation `Validator` trait (`07-forms.md`) via the `Field` wrapper. The `FieldValue::Text` variant receives the joined tag string. For per-tag granularity, register a custom `Validator` that splits the value by the delimiter and validates each segment individually:
1078	
1079	```rust
1080	use ars_forms::{Validator, FieldValue, ValidationContext, ValidationResult, ValidationError, ValidationErrorCode};
1081	
1082	struct PerTagValidator<F: Fn(&str) -> Result<(), String>> {
1083	    delimiter: String,
1084	    validate_tag: F,
1085	}
1086	
1087	impl<F: Fn(&str) -> Result<(), String> + Send + Sync> Validator for PerTagValidator<F> {
1088	    fn validate(&self, value: &FieldValue, _ctx: &ValidationContext) -> ValidationResult {
1089	        let text = match value {
1090	            FieldValue::Text(t) => t.as_str(),
1091	            _ => return ValidationResult::Valid,
1092	        };
1093	        for tag in text.split(&self.delimiter).map(str::trim).filter(|t| !t.is_empty()) {
1094	            if let Err(reason) = (self.validate_tag)(tag) {
1095	                return ValidationResult::Invalid(vec![ValidationError {
1096	                    message: reason.clone(),
1097	                    code: ValidationErrorCode::Custom(reason),
1098	                }]);
1099	            }
1100	        }
1101	        ValidationResult::Valid
1102	    }
1103	}
1104	```
1105	
1106	- **Required validation**: When `required == true`, at least one tag must be present. The `HiddenInput` has `required` set and the empty string value triggers native constraint validation.
1107	- **Max tags**: Enforced by the state machine via `Props.max`. No form-level validator needed.
1108	- **Duplicate prevention**: Enforced by the state machine when `Props.allow_duplicates == false`. No form-level validator needed.
1109	- **Reset behavior**: On form reset, the adapter restores `value` to `default_value`.
1110	- **Disabled/readonly propagation**: When inside a `Field` or `Fieldset`, the adapter merges `disabled`/`readonly` from `FieldCtx` per `07-forms.md` §12.6.
1111	
1112	## 6. Library Parity
1113	
1114	> Compared against: Ark UI (`TagsInput`), React Aria (`TagGroup`).
1115	
1116	Note: Ark UI's `TagsInput` and React Aria's `TagGroup` differ significantly in scope. Ark UI's is an input-focused component (type to add tags); React Aria's is a display-focused component (tag list with remove). ars-ui's `TagsInput` covers both use cases.
1117	
1118	### 6.1 Props
1119	
1120	| Feature                       | ars-ui                          | Ark UI                             | React Aria                             | Notes                                             |
1121	| ----------------------------- | ------------------------------- | ---------------------------------- | -------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- |
1122	| Controlled/uncontrolled value | `value` / `default_value`       | `value` / `defaultValue`           | `selectedKeys` / `defaultSelectedKeys` | React Aria uses selection model, not input model  |
1123	| Max tags                      | `max`                           | `max`                              | --                                     | --                                                |
1124	| Disabled                      | `disabled`                      | `disabled`                         | --                                     | --                                                |
1125	| Read-only                     | `readonly`                      | `readOnly`                         | --                                     | --                                                |
1126	| Invalid                       | `invalid`                       | `invalid`                          | --                                     | --                                                |
1127	| Required                      | `required`                      | `required`                         | --                                     | --                                                |
1128	| Delimiter                     | `delimiter`                     | `delimiter`                        | --                                     | React Aria has no input (display-only)            |
1129	| Add on paste                  | `add_on_paste`                  | `addOnPaste`                       | --                                     | --                                                |
1130	| Allow duplicates              | `allow_duplicates`              | --                                 | --                                     | ars-ui exclusive                                  |
1131	| Max length per tag            | `max_length`                    | `maxLength`                        | --                                     | --                                                |
1132	| Editable (inline edit)        | `editable`                      | `editable`                         | --                                     | --                                                |
1133	| Blur behavior                 | `blur_behavior` (`Add`/`Clear`) | `blurBehavior` (`clear`/`add`)     | --                                     | --                                                |
1134	| Name (form)                   | `name`                          | `name`                             | --                                     | --                                                |
1135	| Placeholder                   | `placeholder`                   | `placeholder`                      | --                                     | --                                                |
1136	| Input value                   | --                              | `inputValue` / `defaultInputValue` | --                                     | Ark UI has controlled input value                 |
1137	| Validate (custom)             | --                              | `validate`                         | --                                     | Ark UI has per-tag validation callback            |
1138	| Selection mode                | --                              | --                                 | `selectionMode`                        | React Aria exclusive (tag selection for bulk ops) |
1139	| Disabled keys                 | --                              | --                                 | `disabledKeys`                         | React Aria exclusive                              |
1140	| Disallow empty selection      | --                              | --                                 | `disallowEmptySelection`               | React Aria exclusive                              |
1141	| Escape key behavior           | --                              | --                                 | `escapeKeyBehavior`                    | React Aria exclusive                              |
1142	| On remove                     | --                              | --                                 | `onRemove`                             | React Aria fires on tag removal                   |
1143	
1144	**Gaps:** None. Ark UI's `inputValue` controlled input is not needed -- ars-ui tracks input value in context. Ark UI's `validate` callback is handled via ars-ui's form integration (`PerTagValidator` in §5). React Aria's `TagGroup` is fundamentally a different component (display-only tag list) and its selection/removal props do not apply to the input-focused `TagsInput`.
1145	
1146	### 6.2 Anatomy
1147	
1148	| Part              | ars-ui              | Ark UI              | React Aria               | Notes                                     |
1149	| ----------------- | ------------------- | ------------------- | ------------------------ | ----------------------------------------- |
1150	| Root              | `Root`              | `Root`              | `TagGroup`               | --                                        |
1151	| Label             | `Label`             | `Label`             | `Label`                  | --                                        |
1152	| Control           | `Control`           | `Control`           | `TagList`                | Wraps tags + input                        |
1153	| Input             | `Input`             | `Input`             | --                       | React Aria has no input                   |
1154	| Item (tag)        | `Item`              | `Item`              | `Tag`                    | --                                        |
1155	| ItemPreview       | `ItemPreview`       | `ItemPreview`       | --                       | Tag visual container                      |
1156	| ItemText          | `ItemText`          | `ItemText`          | --                       | --                                        |
1157	| ItemDeleteTrigger | `ItemDeleteTrigger` | `ItemDeleteTrigger` | --                       | React Aria handles remove via render prop |
1158	| ItemInput         | `ItemInput`         | `ItemInput`         | --                       | Inline edit input                         |
1159	| ClearTrigger      | `ClearTrigger`      | `ClearTrigger`      | --                       | --                                        |
1160	| HiddenInput       | `HiddenInput`       | `HiddenInput`       | --                       | Form submission                           |
1161	| Description       | `Description`       | --                  | `Text[slot=description]` | --                                        |
1162	| ErrorMessage      | `ErrorMessage`      | --                  | `FieldError`             | --                                        |
1163	
1164	**Gaps:** None.
1165	
1166	### 6.3 Events
1167	
1168	| Callback         | ars-ui                    | Ark UI               | React Aria          | Notes                       |
1169	| ---------------- | ------------------------- | -------------------- | ------------------- | --------------------------- |
1170	| Value change     | via `Bindable`            | `onValueChange`      | --                  | --                          |
1171	| Input change     | `Event::InputChange`      | `onInputValueChange` | --                  | --                          |
1172	| Highlight change | via `Context.focused_tag` | `onHighlightChange`  | --                  | --                          |
1173	| Invalid tag      | --                        | `onValueInvalid`     | --                  | ars-ui uses form validation |
1174	| Selection change | --                        | --                   | `onSelectionChange` | React Aria exclusive        |
1175	| Remove           | `Event::RemoveTag`        | --                   | `onRemove`          | --                          |
1176	
1177	**Gaps:** None.
1178	
1179	### 6.4 Features
1180	
1181	| Feature                    | ars-ui | Ark UI | React Aria        |
1182	| -------------------------- | ------ | ------ | ----------------- |
1183	| Add tags by typing         | Yes    | Yes    | No (display-only) |
1184	| Remove tags                | Yes    | Yes    | Yes               |
1185	| Inline editing             | Yes    | Yes    | No                |
1186	| Paste support              | Yes    | Yes    | No                |
1187	| Keyboard navigation (tags) | Yes    | Yes    | Yes               |
1188	| Max tags limit             | Yes    | Yes    | No                |
1189	| Delimiter support          | Yes    | Yes    | No                |
1190	| Blur behavior              | Yes    | Yes    | No                |
1191	| Form integration           | Yes    | Yes    | No                |
1192	| IME composition            | Yes    | --     | --                |
1193	| RTL support                | Yes    | Yes    | Yes               |
1194	
1195	**Gaps:** None.
1196	
1197	### 6.5 Summary
1198	
1199	- **Overall:** Full parity -- no gaps identified.
1200	- **Divergences:** (1) React Aria's `TagGroup` is a display/selection component, not an input component -- it does not support adding tags by typing; ars-ui's `TagsInput` covers both input and display use cases; (2) ars-ui uses form-level validation (`PerTagValidator`) instead of a component-level `validate` callback; (3) ars-ui tracks IME composition state for CJK input support.
1201	- **Recommended additions:** None.
1202

